{
  "texts": [
    "While green finance investments are on the rise, there remains a need for enhanced government policy support, innovation, and public awareness to drive further investments in sustainable projects (Sengupta and Patil, 2023).",
    "The global shift toward a low-carbon, green, and sustainable economy necessitates the development of a financial system that supports sustainable development, presenting worldwide growth opportunities.",
    "This transition requires coordinated efforts from both the public and private sectors to create an enabling environment for sustainable finance.",
    "Green finance mechanisms, such as green bonds and green loans, offer essential capital for developing and scaling renewable energy projects.",
    "This capital is crucial for reducing greenhouse gas emissions and achieving climate targets."
  ]
}